      "acceptanceCriteria": "Number of experimental replicates sufficient to characterize measurement variability; statistical summary (mean, SD, 95% CI) reported for NIH at each operating point.",
      "rationale": "N=5 independent experimental runs performed at each of 5 operating points (25 total). Coefficient of variation for NIH ranges 4.1%–7.8% across operating points. 95% confidence intervals computed and used as reference uncertainty in output comparison."
    },
