    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo UQ confirms 95th-percentile NIH remains below clinical threshold at all operating points. Validation MAE of 8.3% is within acceptable bounds given conservative systematic over-prediction direction. A screening sensitivity study was noted in the UQ narrative as informing input parameter selection and distribution widths; however, no formal structured sensitivity analysis with quantitative importance measures (e.g., Sobol indices) has been linked to this package. The assessment team considers the informal screening sufficient given the conservative direction of model bias and the margin between 95th-percentile NIH and the clinical threshold. Decision: Accepted with recommendation that a formal sensitivity analysis be conducted prior to next design iteration.",
